      "span_text": "Twenty-six HIV/AIDS patients (age: 47.2 ± 9.8 years; 25M/1F; CD4 + T-cell count: 299.5 ± 175.7 per µl; log 10 viral load: 2.57 ± 1.28 RNA copies per ml of blood plasma) and 14 HIV-seronegative controls (age: 37.6 ± 12.2 years; 8M/6F) underwent 3D T1-weighted MRI scanning; subjects and scans were the same as those analyzed in the cortical thickness study in  , where more detailed neuropsychiatric data from the subjects is presented."
